overview: The user initiated a comprehensive aesthetic review for their sleep
  questionnaire app, aiming to elevate its visual appeal from a generic template
  to a more calming and professional sleep-themed experience. The agent
  implemented a new color palette with deep indigos, purples, and teal accents,
  along with custom utility classes for gradients and shadows. Key components
  like the main form layout, progress bar, intro section, and all form fields
  (checkboxes, radio buttons, sliders) were redesigned with improved visual
  hierarchy, interactive states, and subtle decorative elements. All 14
  questionnaire sections were updated to ensure consistent theming, replacing
  old gray boxes with new card-style groupings. During the review, a console
  error related to  values being passed to input components was identified
  and fixed by modifying the  component to safely handle  values.
  The overall outcome is a visually cohesive, polished, and user-friendly sleep
  assessment application.
